		<td><b>Super Mario World Famicom pirate</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Hey guys, this is my first post here, so sorry if this was put in the wrong forum, or this already has a thread.  
<br />
<br />Anyway, I was wondering if this was possible.  I know that there's already a version on a physical cartridge, but it's not the complete version.  The only cartridge I've seen the complete version on is the JY Company 45-in-1.  I've also heard that Mapper 90 games are pretty finicky.  So, my question is this:  If I have a standalone ROM of the full version of SMW, could I write it to a cartridge?

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
