	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />From what I understand (I don't have any mapper 90 carts) they use a 'glob-top' package for those mappers, and in that case it almost always follows that the ROMs are glob-top also.  To quote the magic 8-ball, "outlook not good".  Even so, it's theoretically still possible, but it would be a lot of work (you could scape off the solder-mask and wire to some thin traces on the PCB - assuming all of them are exposed and not under the epoxy blob).

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


