		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">nintendo2600 wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">...why SMW and\or Bio Miricle AKA Baby Mario have never been hacked to a more common mapper</div>
<br />
<br />Mapper 90 is just plain rediculous. I've tried to port SMW, but it just strange in some situations.
<br />
<br />"Mario Baby" hasn't been hacked because the mapper used actually maps areas of WRAM space with PRG-ROM...It's a sinch to get emulated, but it's just plain difficult to port the code to the correct space. Same with Ai Senshi Nicol and SMB2J (Loopy ported SMB2J to MMC3 though).
<br />
<br />P.S.: On the other hand, all the MMC3-compatible games this Person/Group made in the pirate scene seem to work well on stock boards.

		

